that on some frightful slope or blasphemous plateau the crawling chaos waited , carter could not doubt ; and he wished that the suspense might soon be over .
the whining of those impious flutes was shocking , and he would have given worlds for some even sound ; but these had no voices , and the slaves did not talk .
then through that darkness there did come a normal sound .
